Small feature. Add an optional `is_ephemeral` filter to a task-list query (SQLite via Drizzle ORM). The DB column is `is_ephemeral INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0` (0 or 1). Extend the Zod input schema and the store query so a caller can list only ephemeral, or only non-ephemeral, tasks.

```ts
// validation/task.ts
export const taskListInputSchema = z.object({
    session_id: z.string().uuid().optional(),
    status: taskStatusSchema.optional(),
});
```
```ts
// store/task-store.ts — list(filter)
const conditions = [];
if (filter.session_id) conditions.push(eq(tasksTable.sessionId, filter.session_id));
if (filter.status)     conditions.push(eq(tasksTable.status, filter.status));
// …applied via and(...) over `conditions`…
```
Add the `is_ephemeral` filter.
